This anima is the essence of fire, hot to touch and even hotter in temper. They are very common in the Tetraverse. Smolderlings thrive in very hot environments and can emerge in lava amidst volcanic mountains, fire-pits, the open desert amongst many other locations. Although they aren’t the most challenging opponents, their versatile evolution makes them essential to include in any fire-based squad.

From Zarushima, the isolated island in the Earth kingdom region, Zarugami is the first Stage 3 Anima to make an appearance outside of the Tetraverse. This intimidating beast is very dangerous and possessive of its prey. Zarugami never lets opponents flee when caught in its range. Be careful not to approach this Anima in the wild, unless you are fully prepared for deadly combat.

Watch your step, you don’t want to accidentally step on a Turfling. This anima can be located all over the Tetraverse, especially is rich organic soil. Turflings develop a symbiotic relationship with its environment and help plants excel in their growth. Turflings are not cut out for battle but can assist your party in various ways.

This anima is the essence of water, a combination of solid, liquid and gas all in one. They are very common in the Tetraverse. Aqualings thrive in fresh water sources and can be found in rivers, lakes, reservoirs and a variety of other bodies of water. Although they aren’t very strong, Aqualings are very adaptable in their higher stage evolution.
Aerolyn the air bird Anima

In celebration of the 50 year anniversary of Bangladesh, we'd like everyone to give a warm welcome to Panthera, the second Stage-2 Anima we would like you to meet. Panthera's notable size, mobility, and attack power make it a must-have for the battlefield. However, after landing a devastating attack, it might just decide to take a nap. This Anima prototype was inspired by the Bengal Tiger, so it is especially cherished by the creators, who are from Bangladesh.

Forquiles the plant dragon.
Ambrosia's sting packs a punch and leaves its opponents paralyzed or poisoned. This Anima's high mobility allows it to traverse the battlefield swiftly.

Yamagami protects the mountain and many of the Anima who live its vicinity. The tremors caused by Yamagami’s fists can be felt all the way to Iso on the shores of the Earth Kingdom. This Stage 2 Anima boasts high defensive characteristics, making it able to endure many attacks.

Meet Yamazaru, the first Tetraverse Anima starter we are excited to reveal. Don’t be fooled by Yamazaru’s cuteness; if you’re not careful, you may leave without some of your belongings. By themselves, Yamazarus are not very strong but they can usually be found in small groups and like to assist each other in battle and in mischief.

Be careful not to approach this Anima in the wild, unless you are fully prepared for deadly combat.
